The first thing you need to do is test yt-dlp, as distributed.
Make an alias, like this.

alias ytget="yt-dlp -x --audio-format mp3"

ytget means youtube get.
Then try to fetch anything at all.
How bout George Carlin on baseball versus football.

ytget 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IhN1ExFCXNA'

does it come down ok?
Do you have an mp3 file?
If yes, then listen to it, and enjoy it,
and appreciate once again the genius of the man.
If not, then uninstall yt-dlp from your system, get the latest,
build, and install, and hope that version works.

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp
cd yt-dlp
make
sudo make install

Let's assume yt-dlp works, either as distributed or using the latest code.
Now you are on your way.
